The paper presents a novel approach for decoding EEG signals for brain-computer interfaces (BCIs) using boosted convolutional neural networks (ConvNets) and multiwavelet-based time-frequency (TF) causality analysis. The paper involves deep learning techniques and signal processing, which are relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), and signal and image processing (cs.SI).
